        <subsection>
            <title>Cross<ndash/>Referencing Schema</title>
            <introduction>
            <p>To take advantage of cross<ndash/>referencing, which <pretext/> and a digital platform make easy, you will need to provide an <term>xml id</term> to every element that you wish to be able to cross<ndash/>reference. You can find more on <url href="https://pretextbook.org/doc/author-guide/html/topic-cross-referencing.html">cross<ndash/>referencing</url> in the <url href="https://pretextbook.org/doc/author-guide/html/index.html"><pretext/> Author's Guide </url>, so here we only address the schema we (try to) use in <pubtitle>Sound Writing</pubtitle></p>
            </introduction>
            <paragraphs xml:id="par-ag-referencing-schema">
                <title>Assigning xml:id Tags</title>
                <p>Since the handbook was authored over a long period of time and put into <pretext/> by numerous people, the naming conventions for cross<ndash/>referencing are not wholly consistent throughout the handbook. Nevertheless, we recommend that you abide by the following naming practices:
                    <dl>
                        <li>
                            <title><c>&lt;chapter&gt;</c></title>
                            <p><c>xml:id="chapter-name"</c></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <title><c>&lt;section&gt;</c></title>
                            <p><c>xml:id="[one-word-chapter-name]-section-name"</c></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <title><c>&lt;subsection&gt;</c></title>
                            <p><c>xml:id="[one-word-section-name]-subsection-name"</c></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <title><c>&lt;subsubsection&gt;</c></title>
                            <p><c>xml:id="[one-word-subsection-name]-subsubsection-name"</c></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <title><c>&lt;paragraphs&gt;</c></title>
                            <p><c>xml:id="par-[one-word-parent-division-name]-paragraphs-title"</c></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <title><c>&lt;list&gt;</c></title>
                            <p><c>xml:id="list-[one-word-section-name]-abbreviated-list-title"</c></p>
                        </li>
                    </dl>
                </p>
            </paragraphs>
        </subsection>
        
